  "prompt": "How do I become a sub inspector in delhi police after graduation?",
  "response": "To become a Sub Inspector (SI) in the Delhi Police after graduation, you need to follow these steps:\n\n### Eligibility Criteria:\n1. **Educational Qualification**: You must have a Bachelor\u2019s degree from a recognized university.\n2. **Age Limit**: The age should be between 20 to 25 years. Age relaxation is applicable for candidates belonging to reserved categories (SC/ST/OBC).\n3. **Physical Standards**: You must meet the physical standards set by the Delhi Police.\n\n### Selection Process:\nThe selection process for the Sub Inspector in Delhi Police involves several stages:\n\n1. **Written Examination**:\n   - **Paper I**: It is an objective type paper consisting of General Intelligence and Reasoning, General Knowledge and Awareness, Quantitative Aptitude, and English Comprehension.\n   - **Paper II**: It is a descriptive type paper where you need to write an essay and a letter or a precis.\n\n2. **Physical Endurance and Measurement Test (PE&MT)**:\n   - This test includes various physical activities like running, long jump, high jump, etc. You need to meet the specific standards set by the Delhi Police.\n\n3. **Medical Examination**:\n   - You need to undergo a medical examination to ensure you are medically fit for the job.\n\n4. **Document Verification**:\n   - After passing all the above stages, your documents will be verified to confirm your eligibility.\n\n### How to Apply:\n1. **Visit the Official Website**: Go to the official website of the Staff Selection Commission (SSC) which conducts the recruitment for Delhi Police SI.\n2. **Registration**: Register yourself on the SSC website and fill out the application form for the Sub Inspector in Delhi Police.\n3. **Application Fee**: Pay the required application fee online. Fee waivers are available for certain categories.\n4. **Download Admit Card**: Once the application process is complete, download the admit card for the written examination from the SSC website.\n\n### Preparation Tips:\n1. **Study Material**: Use standard books and study material for the preparation of the written examination.\n2. **Mock Tests**: Take mock tests and previous year question papers to understand the exam pattern and improve your speed and accuracy.\n3. **Physical Fitness**: Maintain a good level of physical fitness by regular exercise and training.\n4. **Current Affairs**: Keep yourself updated with current affairs and general knowledge.\n\n### Additional Tips:\n- **Stay Updated**: Keep an eye on the official SSC website for the latest notifications and updates regarding the recruitment process.\n- **Practice Regularly**: Regular practice and revision are key to cracking the written examination.\n- **Healthy Lifestyle**: Maintain a healthy lifestyle to stay fit for the physical tests.\n\nBy following these steps and tips, you can increase your chances of becoming a Sub Inspector in the Delhi Police. Good luck!",
